## Hints for Future Agents
- Env remaps deliberately use plain model IDs; only the top-level "model" key
  carries the [1m] 1M-context suffix. Subagents/aliases run the standard
  context window.
- No ANTHROPIC_DEFAULT_OPUS_MODEL remap was added: the opus alias is unused in
  this setup (top-level model pins fable directly), and adding a fourth remap
  would be speculative. If something starts requesting "opus" and should get
  Fable, add that remap then.
- Cost caveat: the haiku alias now resolves to Opus 4.8, so anything that
  picks haiku for cheap/fast work (background tasks, summarizers) silently
  runs on Opus pricing/latency.

## Codebase Discoveries
This is the third iteration of this pattern; 5897f5e did the same bump when
Opus 4.8 became the ceiling. When a new top model ships, expect this exact
one-rung shift plus a possible plugin prompt retune (cf. 60d6907 "retune
prompts for Opus 4.8").

